{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":610,"text":"What do you do if you had\nto figure out the information"},{"time":3290,"text":"behind 11.5 million documents,"},{"time":5715,"text":"verify it and make sense of it?"},{"time":8150,"text":"That was a challenge"},{"time":9326,"text":"that a group of journalists\nhad to face late last year."},{"time":12662,"text":"An anonymous person\ncalling himself John Doe"},{"time":16122,"text":"had somehow managed to copy\nnearly 40 years of records"},{"time":19198,"text":"of the Panamanian law firm\nMossack Fonseca."},{"time":23317,"text":"This is one of many firms around the world"},{"time":26031,"text":"that specialize in setting up accounts\nin offshore tax havens"},{"time":29586,"text":"like the British Virgin Islands,"},{"time":31610,"text":"for rich and powerful people\nwho like to keep secrets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36195,"text":"John Doe had managed to copy\nevery spreadsheet from this firm,"},{"time":39757,"text":"every client file,"},{"time":41375,"text":"every email,"},{"time":43098,"text":"from 1977 to the present day."},{"time":46912,"text":"It represented the biggest cache"},{"time":49251,"text":"of inside information\ninto the tax haven system"},{"time":52061,"text":"that anyone had ever seen."},{"time":54092,"text":"But it also presented a gigantic challenge\nto investigative journalism."},{"time":59870,"text":"Think about it:\n11.5 million documents,"},{"time":64335,"text":"containing the secrets of people\nfrom more than 200 different countries."},{"time":68449,"text":"Where do you start\nwith such a vast resource?"},{"time":70950,"text":"Where do you even begin to tell a story"},{"time":73053,"text":"that can trail off\ninto every corner of the globe,"},{"time":76367,"text":"and that can affect almost\nany person in any language,"},{"time":79436,"text":"sometimes in ways\nthey don't even know yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82513,"text":"John Doe had given the information\nto two journalists"},{"time":85039,"text":"at the German newspaper\nSüddeutsche Zeitung."},{"time":88562,"text":"He said he was motivated\nby -- and I quote --"},{"time":91820,"text":"\"The scale of the injustice\nthat the documents would reveal.\""},{"time":96401,"text":"But one user alone can never make sense"},{"time":98408,"text":"of such a vast amount of information."},{"time":100362,"text":"So the Süddeutsche Zeitung reached out"},{"time":102248,"text":"to my organization in Washington, DC,"},{"time":105016,"text":"The International Consortium\nof Investigative Journalists."},{"time":109926,"text":"We decided to do something\nthat was the very opposite"},{"time":112524,"text":"of everything we'd been taught\nto do as journalists:"},{"time":115289,"text":"share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116468,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118324,"text":"By nature, investigative\nreporters are lone wolves."},{"time":122002,"text":"We fiercely guard our secrets,"},{"time":123855,"text":"at times even from our editors,"},{"time":125413,"text":"because we know that the moment\nwe tell them what we have,"},{"time":128297,"text":"they'll want that story right away."},{"time":130691,"text":"And to be frank,"},{"time":132607,"text":"when you get a good story,"},{"time":134053,"text":"you like to keep the glory to yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137733,"text":"But there's no doubt\nthat we live in a shrinking world,"},{"time":140366,"text":"and that the media has largely\nbeen slow to wake up to this."},{"time":143559,"text":"The issues we report on\nare more and more transnational."},{"time":147135,"text":"Giant corporations operate\non a global level."},{"time":150441,"text":"Environmental and health\ncrises are global."},{"time":153758,"text":"So, too, are financial flows\nand financial crises."},{"time":157488,"text":"So it seems staggering\nthat journalism has been so late"},{"time":160516,"text":"to cover stories in a truly global way."},{"time":163783,"text":"And it also seems staggering\nthat journalism has been so slow"},{"time":166811,"text":"to wake up to the possibilities\nthat technology brings,"},{"time":170244,"text":"rather than being frightened of it."},{"time":173666,"text":"The reason journalists\nare scared of technology is this:"},{"time":177477,"text":"the profession's largest institutions\nare going through tough times"},{"time":181061,"text":"because of the changing way\nthat people are consuming news."},{"time":184958,"text":"The advertising business models\nthat have sustained reporting are broken."},{"time":189890,"text":"And this has plunged\njournalism into crisis,"},{"time":192572,"text":"forcing those institutions\nto reexamine how they function."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198258,"text":"But where there is crisis,"},{"time":199935,"text":"there is also opportunity."},{"time":202013,"text":"The first challenge presented"},{"time":203491,"text":"by what would eventually become\nknown as the Panama Papers"},{"time":206363,"text":"was to make the documents\nsearchable and readable."},{"time":208936,"text":"There were nearly five million emails,"},{"time":211587,"text":"two million PDFs that needed\nto be scanned and indexed,"},{"time":214924,"text":"and millions more files\nand other kinds of documents."},{"time":218162,"text":"They all needed to be housed\nin a safe and secure location"},{"time":221023,"text":"in the cloud."},{"time":222961,"text":"We next invited reporters\nto have a look at the documents."},{"time":226456,"text":"In all, reporters from more\nthan 100 media organizations"},{"time":230340,"text":"in 76 countries --"},{"time":232433,"text":"from the BBC in Britain"},{"time":234502,"text":"to Le Monde newspaper in France"},{"time":236742,"text":"to the Asahi Shimbun in Japan."},{"time":240473,"text":"\"Native eyes on native names,\"\nwe called it, the idea being,"},{"time":244247,"text":"who best to tell you\nwho was important to Nigeria"},{"time":247630,"text":"than a Nigerian journalist?"},{"time":249623,"text":"Who best in Canada than a Canadian?"},{"time":252247,"text":"There were only two rules\nfor everyone who was invited:"},{"time":255327,"text":"we all agreed to share everything\nthat we found with everybody else,"},{"time":260335,"text":"and we all agreed to publish\ntogether on the same day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263769,"text":"We chose our media partners based on trust"},{"time":265828,"text":"that had been built up through\nprevious smaller collaborations"},{"time":269070,"text":"and also from leads\nthat jumped out from the documents."},{"time":272625,"text":"Over the next few months,"},{"time":273884,"text":"my small nonprofit organization\nof less than 20 people"},{"time":276566,"text":"was joined by more than 350 other\nreporters from 25 language groups."},{"time":282035,"text":"The biggest information leak in history"},{"time":283981,"text":"had now spawned the biggest\njournalism collaboration in history:"},{"time":288091,"text":"376 sets of native eyes doing\nwhat journalists normally never do,"},{"time":294203,"text":"working shoulder to shoulder,"},{"time":295838,"text":"sharing information,"},{"time":297488,"text":"but telling no one."},{"time":300102,"text":"For it became clear at this point"},{"time":301725,"text":"that in order to make\nthe biggest kind of noise,"},{"time":304106,"text":"we first needed\nthe biggest kind of silence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308490,"text":"To manage the project\nover the many months it would take,"},{"time":311244,"text":"we built a secure virtual newsroom."},{"time":313085,"text":"We used encrypted communication systems,"},{"time":316157,"text":"and we built a specially\ndesigned search engine."},{"time":318871,"text":"Inside the virtual newsroom,"},{"time":320522,"text":"the reporters could gather\naround the themes"},{"time":322633,"text":"that were emerging from the documents."},{"time":324638,"text":"Those interested in blood diamonds\nor exotic art, for instance,"},{"time":329968,"text":"could share information about how\nthe offshore world was being used"},{"time":333182,"text":"to hide the trade in both\nof those commodities."},{"time":335413,"text":"Those interested in sport\ncould share information"},{"time":337877,"text":"about how famous sports stars\nwere putting their image rights"},{"time":341166,"text":"into offshore companies,"},{"time":342714,"text":"thereby likely avoiding taxes"},{"time":345001,"text":"in the countries\nwhere they plied their trade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348097,"text":"But perhaps most exciting of all"},{"time":349909,"text":"were the number of world leaders\nand elect politicians"},{"time":353410,"text":"that were emerging from the documents --"},{"time":356540,"text":"figures like Petro Poroshenko in Ukraine,"},{"time":360824,"text":"close associates\nof Vladimir Putin in Russia"},{"time":365852,"text":"and the British Prime Minister,\nDavid Cameron, who is linked"},{"time":369033,"text":"through his late father, Ian Cameron."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372529,"text":"Buried in the documents\nwere secret offshore entities,"},{"time":375784,"text":"such as Wintris Inc.,"},{"time":378427,"text":"a company in the British Virgin Islands"},{"time":380327,"text":"that had actually belonged\nto the sitting Icelandic prime minister."},{"time":384435,"text":"I like to refer to Johannes Kristjansson,"},{"time":386870,"text":"the Icelandic reporter\nwe invited to join the project,"},{"time":389811,"text":"as the loneliest man in the world."},{"time":392231,"text":"For nine months, he refused paid work"},{"time":394544,"text":"and lived off the earnings of his wife."},{"time":397308,"text":"He pasted tarps\nover the windows of his home"},{"time":399415,"text":"to prevent prying eyes\nduring the long Icelandic winter."},{"time":403505,"text":"And he soon ran out of excuses\nto explain his many absences,"},{"time":407327,"text":"as he worked red-eyed,"},{"time":408917,"text":"night after night,"},{"time":410147,"text":"month after month."},{"time":411972,"text":"In all that time, he sat on information"},{"time":414344,"text":"that would eventually bring down\nthe leader of his country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418100,"text":"Now, when you're an investigative reporter\nand you make an amazing discovery,"},{"time":421813,"text":"such as your prime minster can be linked\nto a secret offshore company,"},{"time":425718,"text":"that that company has a financial\ninterest in Icelandic banks --"},{"time":429868,"text":"the very issue he's been elected on --"},{"time":432242,"text":"well, your instinct\nis to scream out very loud."},{"time":436044,"text":"Instead, as one of the few people\nthat he could speak to,"},{"time":438962,"text":"Johannes and I shared\na kind of gallows humor."},{"time":442391,"text":"\"Wintris is coming,\" he used to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444136,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":445689,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":449314,"text":"We were big fans of \"Game of Thrones.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":452759,"text":"When reporters like Johannes\nwanted to scream,"},{"time":455919,"text":"they did so inside the virtual newsroom,"},{"time":458618,"text":"and then they turned\nthose screams into stories"},{"time":460861,"text":"by going outside the documents\nto court records,"},{"time":464479,"text":"official company registers,"},{"time":466163,"text":"and by eventually putting questions\nto those that we intended to name."},{"time":471178,"text":"Panama Papers actually allowed\nthe reporters to look at the world"},{"time":475234,"text":"through a different lens\nfrom everybody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477874,"text":"As we were researching the story,"},{"time":479818,"text":"unconnected to us,"},{"time":481260,"text":"a major political bribery scandal\nhappened in Brazil."},{"time":485339,"text":"A new leader was elected in Argentina."},{"time":488608,"text":"The FBI began to indict officials at FIFA,"},{"time":492523,"text":"the organization that controls\nthe world of professional soccer."},{"time":497089,"text":"The Panama Papers\nactually had unique insights"},{"time":499390,"text":"into each one of these unfolding events."},{"time":501660,"text":"So you can imagine the pressure\nand the ego dramas"},{"time":505124,"text":"that could have ruined\nwhat we were trying to do."},{"time":507637,"text":"Any of one of these journalists,"},{"time":509199,"text":"they could have broken the pact."},{"time":510944,"text":"But they didn't."},{"time":512464,"text":"And on April 3 this year,"},{"time":514056,"text":"at exactly 8pm German time,"},{"time":516261,"text":"we published simultaneously\nin 76 countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520220,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":531640,"text":"The Panama Papers quickly became\none of the biggest stories of the year."},{"time":535276,"text":"This is the scene in Iceland\nthe day after we published."},{"time":538504,"text":"It was the first of many protests."},{"time":541047,"text":"The Icelandic prime minister\nhad to resign."},{"time":543431,"text":"It was a first of many resignations."},{"time":546275,"text":"We spotlighted many famous people\nsuch as Lionel Messi,"},{"time":549862,"text":"the most famous\nsoccer player in the world."},{"time":552726,"text":"And there were some\nunintended consequences."},{"time":555454,"text":"These alleged members\nof a Mexican drug cartel were arrested"},{"time":559155,"text":"after we published details\nabout their hideout."},{"time":562615,"text":"They'd been using the address"},{"time":564579,"text":"to register their offshore company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566573,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":571091,"text":"There's a kind of irony\nin what we've been able to do."},{"time":573676,"text":"The technology -- the Internet --\nthat has broken the business model"},{"time":577406,"text":"is allowing us to reinvent\njournalism itself."},{"time":580516,"text":"And this dynamic is producing"},{"time":582228,"text":"unprecedented levels\nof transparency and impact."},{"time":585772,"text":"We showed how a group of journalists\ncan effect change across the world"},{"time":589282,"text":"by applying new methods\nand old-fashioned journalism techniques"},{"time":593286,"text":"to vast amounts of leaked information."},{"time":596319,"text":"We put all-important context\naround what was given to us by John Doe."},{"time":601205,"text":"And by sharing resources,"},{"time":602814,"text":"we were able to dig deep --"},{"time":604527,"text":"much deeper and longer than most\nmedia organizations allow these days,"},{"time":608926,"text":"because of financial concerns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611500,"text":"Now, it was a big risk,"},{"time":613107,"text":"and it wouldn't work for every story,"},{"time":615119,"text":"but we showed with the Panama Papers"},{"time":617147,"text":"that you can write about any country\nfrom just about anywhere,"},{"time":620109,"text":"and then choose your preferred\nbattleground to defend your work."},{"time":624195,"text":"Try obtaining a court injunction"},{"time":625794,"text":"that would prevent the telling\nof a story in 76 different countries."},{"time":630377,"text":"Try stopping the inevitable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633353,"text":"Shortly after we published,\nI got a three-word text from Johannes:"},{"time":637804,"text":"\"Wintris has arrived.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":640046,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":641468,"text":"It had arrived and so, too, perhaps\nhas a new era for journalism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645673,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646853,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":657612,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Gerard, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659296,"text":"I guess you're going to send\nthat applause to the 350 journalists"},{"time":662395,"text":"who worked with you, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":663997,"text":"Now, a couple of questions\nI would like to ask."},{"time":666232,"text":"The first one is,"},{"time":667423,"text":"you'd been working\nin secrecy for over a year"},{"time":670115,"text":"with 350-something colleagues\nfrom all over the world --"},{"time":673765,"text":"was there ever a moment when you thought"},{"time":677120,"text":"that the leak may be leaked,"},{"time":679272,"text":"that the collaboration may just be broken"},{"time":681999,"text":"by somebody publishing a story?"},{"time":683602,"text":"Or somebody not in the group\nreleasing some information"},{"time":686444,"text":"that they got to know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":688228,"text":"Gerard Ryle: We had a series\nof crises along the way,"},{"time":690904,"text":"including when something major\nwas happening in the world,"},{"time":693659,"text":"the journalists from that country\nwanted to publish right away."},{"time":696706,"text":"We had to calm them down."},{"time":697939,"text":"Probably the biggest crisis we had\nwas a week before publication."},{"time":701107,"text":"We'd sent a series of questions\nto the associates of Vladimir Putin,"},{"time":705142,"text":"but instead of responding,"},{"time":706659,"text":"the Kremlin actually held\na press conference and denounced us,"},{"time":709646,"text":"and denounced the whole thing\nas being, I guess, a plot from the West."},{"time":713087,"text":"At that point, Putin thought\nit was just about him."},{"time":716127,"text":"And, of course, a lot of editors\naround the world"},{"time":718655,"text":"were very nervous about this."},{"time":720380,"text":"They thought the story\nwas going to get out."},{"time":722467,"text":"You can imagine the amount\nof time they'd spent,"},{"time":724744,"text":"the amount of resources,\nmoney spent on this."},{"time":726927,"text":"So I had to basically spend\nthe last week calming everyone down,"},{"time":729988,"text":"a bit like a general,\nwhere you're holding your troops back:"},{"time":732894,"text":"\"Calm, remain calm.\""},{"time":734218,"text":"And then eventually,\nof course, they all did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737323,"text":"BG: And then a couple weeks ago or so,"},{"time":739815,"text":"you released a lot of the documents\nas an open database"},{"time":743808,"text":"for everybody to search\nvia keyword, essentially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747029,"text":"GR: We very much believe"},{"time":748218,"text":"that the basic information\nabout the offshore world"},{"time":750644,"text":"should be made public."},{"time":751821,"text":"Now, we didn't publish\nthe underlying documents"},{"time":754722,"text":"of the journalists we're working with."},{"time":756611,"text":"But the basic information\nsuch as the name of a person,"},{"time":759217,"text":"what their offshore company was\nand the name of that company,"},{"time":762165,"text":"is now all available online."},{"time":763545,"text":"In fact, the biggest resource\nof its kind basically is out there now"}]},{"cues":[{"time":768374,"text":"BG: Gerard, thank you for the work you do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770271,"text":"GR: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771453,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}